%N A179584 Number of permutations of 1..n+9 with deficiencies #{i : p(i) < i} exceeding exceedances #{i : p(i) > i} by n or more.
%C A179584 Added a(0) = 223000 for the number of permutations of [1..9] that have number of deficiencies >= exceedances. Actually, a(-k) would make sense up to k = 9... It might have been more natural to choose as index the size of the set rather than the minimum excess of deficiencies. - _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 21 2026
%H A179584 M. F. Hasler and R. J. Mathar, <a href="/A179582/a179582_3.pdf">Hardin's exceedance excesses A179579-A179582</a>, July 2026.
%H A179584 <a href="/index/Rec#order_20">OEIS Index to entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, order 20.
%F A179584 a(n) = A179583(n+1) + A179576(n). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 18 2026
%F A179584 a(n) = 4^(n + 8)*(n + 13) + 3^(n + 5)*(n + 9)*(n^2 - 48*n - 664)/2 + 2^(n + 1)*(n + 8)*(n + 9)*(n^3 - 92*n^2 + 117*n + 9990)/15 + (n + 7)*(n + 8)*(n + 9)*(n^4 - 59*n^3 + 224*n^2 + 6824*n + 12120)/5040. - _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 18 2026
%F A179584 G.f.: ( 223000 -7598465*x +121607530*x^2 -1214970620*x^3 +8493965334*x^4 -44138326881*x^5 +176746168346*x^6 -557945234838*x^7 +1408591011750*x^8 -2868264348668*x^9 +4729083847216*x^10 -6312048962792*x^11 +6791150962624*x^12 -5837714395360*x^13 +3950716440320*x^14 -2057017036928*x^15 +794630586624*x^16 -214377684480*x^17 +36033085440*x^18 -2839339008*x^19 ) / ( (-1+4*x)^2*(-1+3*x)^4*(2*x-1)^6*(x-1)^8 ). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 22 2026
%o A179584 (PARI) A179584(n) = 4^(n + 8)*(n + 13) + 3^(n + 5)*(n + 9)*(n^2 - 48*n - 664)/2 + 2^(n + 1)*(n + 8)*(n + 9)*(n^3 - 92*n^2 + 117*n + 9990)/15 + (n + 7)*(n + 8)*(n + 9)*(n^4 - 59*n^3 + 224*n^2 + 6824*n + 12120)/5040 \\ same as formula; added upon request. - _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 18 2026
